Hey guys,

I have been working to test swerve code on our robot before competition and am currently running into an issue where one of our swerve modules does not go to the same position as all of the other ones and I believe I have tried just about everything to get it to work.

Originally we put the base on the floor and drove it but we noticed a wheel dragging so we put it back on the cart and saw that one of the wheels was just in a very wrong position. I put it back up on a cart and changed the inversions to no avail. After more testing I decided to change the cancoder as well as the offsets, after a good bit it began to be completely out of wack again. We then changed the steer motor to the same problem.

I have tried a new module wired in to our back left (the problem module) and the back right module to make sure it’s not the module.

Lastly we changed from the canivore to the Rio bus to see if it changed anything and it didn’t.

I’m about out of options and I don’t really know what to do or trouble shoot anymore.

I have reached out to CTR support and am awaiting a response

I’d appreciate any and all advice anyone has.
